Input sample:  Question: Mohammad has 80 bags of chips. One quarter of the bags of chips are Doritos. If Mohammad wants to split the bags of Doritos into 4 equal piles, how many bags of Doritos will be in each pile?
Answer: The number of Dorito bags is 80 / 4 = <<80/4=20>>20 bags
The number of Dorito bags in each pile is 20 / 4 = <<20/4=5>>5 bags

